17/01/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic announced on Monday (16 January) that the planned independence referendum likely would be held in the second half of April. He reiterated that it would be held in full compliance with the highest international standards. 
Separately Monday, President Filip Vujanovic discussed the referendum with Pope Benedict XVI at the Vatican. Vujanovic later told reporters that he and the pontiff had agreed that relations between the Roman Catholic and Orthodox Churches in Montenegro are excellent. (Danas - 17/01/06; Tanjug - 16/01/06)
